Class ProductPartitionNode

      • removeCustomParameter

        @CanIgnoreReturnValue
public ProductPartitionNode removeCustomParameter(String key)
        Removes the specified key from the custom parameters map. The key must be present in the map.

        Since this method follows the standard builder pattern and returns this, there is no way to indicate if the remove operation failed besides throwing an exception.

        Parameters:
        key - the key to remove. This must not be null.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if this node is not a biddable UNIT node
        IllegalArgumentException - if there is no entry for key in the map
